Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Boil a full #kettle{}.

Drain and rinse the @chickpeas{1%carton} in a #sieve{}, then pat dry with #kitchen paper{}.

Spread the chickpeas onto a #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @olive oil{}, sprinkle over the
@roasted spice and herb blend{1%sachet}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat.

Roast on the middle shelf of your oven until crispy, ~{16-18%minutes}. Carefully remove from
the oven and turn halfway through.

Pour the boiled water into a #saucepan{} with @salt{0.5%tsp} and bring back to the boil.

When the pan of water is boiling, add the @orzo{180%g} and bring back to the boil. Cook
until tender, ~{10%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a sieve and run under cold water. Drizzle with oil and stir through to
stop it sticking together.

While the chickpeas roast, zest and halve the @lemon{1/2}.

In a large #bowl{}, combine the @pesto{64%g}, lemon juice, @olive oil{1%tbsp}(for the
dressing) and a pinch of salt and pepper. Set your dressing aside.

Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125%g}.

Stir the tomatoes through the dressing and set aside to macerate.

When the chickpeas have 10 mins remaining, add the @British smoked bacon lardons{90%g} to
the baking tray. Pop into the oven and roast until golden, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook it thoroughly.

When the chickpeas have 5 mins remaining, remove the tray from the oven. Drizzle the
@honey{1%tbsp} over the chickpeas, toss to coat, then return to the oven for the remaining
time.

When everything's ready, add the cooked orzo, @wild rocket{40%g} and half the chickpeas to
the dressing bowl. Mix to combine.

> TIP: Don't add the leaves too early or they'll go soggy.

Share your orzo salad between your serving #bowls{}.

Top with the remaining chickpeas and crumble over the @Greek style salad cheese{50%g}.

Sprinkle over a pinch of lemon zest to finish. Enjoy!